<h2 class='date-header'>Saturday, November 25, 2017</h2>
<div class='post hentry'>
<a name='558687070678313991'></a>
<h3 class='post-title entry-title'>
<a href='http://www.electric-vehiclenews.com/2017/11/renault-samsung-unveil-new-sm3-ze-with.html'>Renault Samsung unveil new SM3 Z.E with 36 kWh battery</a>
</h3>
<div class='post-header-line-1'></div>
<div class='post-body entry-content'>
<p><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="https://4.bp.blogspot.com/-5v1d1aV-uXA/WhoUwU5WYLI/AAAAAAAANlo/lKRk3Yjo3j49LvirPF4GoZp0jgm_i3qtQCLcBGAs/s1600/SM3_Z_E.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" data-original-height="767" data-original-width="1600" height="192" src="https://4.bp.blogspot.com/-5v1d1aV-uXA/WhoUwU5WYLI/AAAAAAAANlo/lKRk3Yjo3j49LvirPF4GoZp0jgm_i3qtQCLcBGAs/s400/SM3_Z_E.jpg" width="400" /></a></div>
<p>
Renault Samsung Motors have unveiled the new SM3 Z.E. at the Daegu International Future Auto Expo in South Korea. Determined to upgrade its electric vehicle range to meet customer demand, and buoyed by the EV expertise it has gained over the past eight years, Groupe Renault is continuing to renew its line-up, the latest example being the new version of the SM3 Z.E. which first appeared in 2013.
<p>
The autonomy of the Renault Samsung Motors SM3 Z.E. &#8211; the market&#8217;s only three-box saloon &#8211; has been increased by 57 percent to 213 kilometres based on the Korean type approval cycle.
<p>
Battery power has been upped to 36kWh with no increase in weight and, with the average daily trip in South Korea standing at 40 kilometres in 2016 according to a Korean Transportation Safety Authority (KOTSA) report, the new SM3 Z.E. is capable of running for approximately five days on a single charge.
<p>
This increase in autonomy and the model&#8217;s spacious cabin will permit the SM3 Z.E. to address the strong demand expressed not only by retail customers, but also by state-run fleets and taxi operators. Indeed, 1,200 cars were purchased by South Korea&#8217;s Ministry of Health and Welfare last April, while the model is also popular as an EV taxi in Seoul, Daegu and Jeju Island.</p>
